    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-04-05T09:29:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-04-05T09:29:00-05:00" n="695"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d695">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">751G.5/4–554: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in France</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d695fn1">Drafted by the Secretary of State. Secretary
                            <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">Dulles</persName> transmitted the text of
                        this telegram to London for Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_AWW1"
                            >Aldrich</persName> in telegram 5181, Apr. 5. (751G.5/4–554)</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret<lb/>priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-04-05T09:29:00-05:00"
                            >April 5, 1954—9:29 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3482. Eyes only for Ambassador from Secretary. As I personally explained to
                        <persName corresp="#p_EGP1">Ely</persName> in presence of <persName
                        corresp="#p_PAAW1">Radford</persName>, it is not possible for US to commit
                    belligerent acts in Indochina without full political understanding with France
                    and other countries. In addition, Congressional action would be required. After
                    conference at highest level, I must confirm this position. US is doing
                    everything possible as indicated my 5175<note n="2" xml:id="d695fn2">See <ref
                            target="#d687fn1">footnote 1, p. 1225</ref>.</note> to prepare public,
                    Congressional and Constitutional basis for united action in Indochina. However,
                    such action is impossible except on coalition basis with active British
                    Commonwealth participation. Meanwhile US prepared, as has been demonstrated, to
                    do everything short of belligerency.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_FYI1">FYI</gloss> US cannot and will not be put in position of
                    alone salvaging British Commonwealth interests in Malaya, Australia and New
                    Zealand. This matter now under discussion with UK at highest level.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
